My name is Maria, Im a new repatriate from Russia, made an Aliyah in April. I work as a senior system
analyst, a senior business analyst, a team leader and a project manager.
Understanding the importance of language in my profession, Im actively studying Hebrew. Now I hope to
find a position of junior/middle system and business analyst or QA tester that will give me the opportunity to
apply my skills and develop as I learn Hebrew.
I really love my job so Im ready to work hard and learn fast to develop rapidly in analytics and leadership in
new conditions.
I started my career as SQL and PL/SQL developer. Then I changed my profile to a system and business
analyst, combining these roles and role of QA tester throughout my career. Thanks to communication skills,
high level of emotional intelligence and the ability to see the big picture, took the team leader position. Later,
became the leader of several teams, combining leadership with the role of an analyst. Have also been the
project manager of several projects.
Now I have extensive experience in system analytics, business analytics, QA and management. Many years of
experience working for the largest banks in Russia. Research, definition, optimization and automation of
business processes, development of management and analytical reporting, all types of manual testing, team
management and project management. Work experience with Jira, Confluence, Visio, TFS, PowerPoint,
Visual Studio Code, MS Project, Oracle SQL Navigator, MS SQL Management studio etc. Using waterfall,
scram, kanban.
Some of my projects:
 Electronic document management for cash deposit and withdrawal (Alfa-Bank). 90% of transactions
go through EDM.
 Complete automation of deal making processes for collection and self-collection (Alfa-Bank).
 Integration of electronic document storage system with the main bank's systems. Standardization of the
integration process for quick connection of systems (Alfa-Bank).
 Field Staff Management System of the Technical Support Department of Sberbank (AT Consulting).
 System for monitoring and analyzing the activities of internal structural divisions of Sberbank (AT
Consulting).
